{
  "texts": [
    "We found differences in performance between frontal and non-frontal tumors (Fig. 5f).",
    "Despite not being significant (p = 0.12, two-tailed U-test), frontal tumors showed higher PCC (0.817 ± 0.002 [mean ± SEM]) than temporal and parietal together (0.789 ± 0.003 [mean ± SEM]).",
    "Lastly, and contrary to what we observed in functional dynamics, the results of FCNET were not sensitive to whether the tumor intersected the ventricles (p = 0.82, two-tailed U-test).",
    "We also tested the topology of the generated networks by computing the weight probability distribution.",
    "The loss function used to train all models did not have any topological term, but the generated networks shared global properties with the ground truth as measured by the KL and JS divergences in Table 1."
  ]
}